                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On Thursday, April 22, 1954, at 4 p.m., Secretary of State <persName
                        corresp="#p_DJF1">John Foster Dulles</persName>, British Foreign Secretary
                        <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Anthony Eden</persName>, and French Foreign
                    Minister <persName corresp="#p_BG1">Georges Bidault</persName> met at the Quai
                    d’Orsay to discuss the Geneva Conference, which convened on April 26. For the
                    record of this tripartite meeting, see <ref target="frus1952-54v16#pg_544"
                        >volume XVI, page 544</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
